# Trivy vulnerability suppressions
# Review monthly and remove entries when upstream fixes are available.

# lazygit v0.59.0 (latest) built with Go 1.25.6 — needs Go 1.25.7+ for fix.
# Upstream issue: jesseduffield/lazygit hasn't released a rebuild yet.
# Risk: crypto/tls session resumption — lazygit doesn't expose TLS services.
CVE-2025-68121

# node-tar transitive dependency in globally-installed npm CLIs
# (claude-unleashed, @openai/codex, @google/gemini-cli, opencode-ai).
# These CLIs don't process untrusted tar archives at runtime.
# Fix available (tar 7.5.3-7.5.8) but upstream packages haven't updated.
CVE-2026-23745
CVE-2026-23950
CVE-2026-24842
CVE-2026-26960

# glob/minimatch transitive deps in globally-installed npm CLIs.
# glob 10.4.5 command injection requires malicious filenames — CLIs don't
# process user-controlled filenames in glob context.
# minimatch 9.0.5-9.0.6 DoS via crafted patterns — CLIs use hardcoded patterns.
CVE-2025-64756
CVE-2026-26996
